> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //**SCP-7478** emerges from the tunnel. It is holding a box.// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
>  
> **SCP-7478:** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]This is what you want. This is what you've //always// wanted.[[/span]]
>  
> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //**Elane** staggers back, shaking her head. Her eyes are wide and her gaze is fixed on **SCP-7478**.// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
>  
> **Elane:** NO! NO, YOU'RE IN MY HEAD, //YOU'RE IN MY HEAD!//
>  
> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //**SCP-7478** holds the box out towards **Elane**.// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
>  
> **SCP-7478:** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]It is not something you can deny. As clear as the sun. As powerful as the burning light of billions of quasars.[[/span]]
>  
> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //**SCP-7478** opens the box. **Elane** screams and covers her face with her arms.// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
>  
> **Elane:** NO! NO, //STAY AWAY! STAY AWAY FROM ME!//
> 
> **SCP-7478:** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]They fill the night sky.[[/span]]
>  
> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //**Something** is inside the box. That **something** moves.// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
>  
> **SCP-7478:** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]They fill it with nothing but sunburn.[[/span]]
>  
> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //The **something** slithers out of the box. It leaves behind a faint trail of a clear, thin, almost greasy liquid. It falls to the floor with a wet splat before it twitches towards **Elane**. **Elane** backs into a wall behind her, slowly sliding to the ground with her arms still covering her face. Muffled weeping is heard. **SCP-7478** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]chuckles[[/span]], brushing its hair away from its eyes.// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
>  
> **SCP-7478:** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]You're already here. You've always been here. This is just another step down the spire.[[/span]]
>  
> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //The **something** touches **Elane's** leg. Wet, stringy filaments clinging to the fabric of her clothes. She screams again, and it echoes throughout the tunnel.// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
>  
> **SCP-7478:** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]It is alright. You will be repurposed soon.[[/span]]
> 
> **SCP-7478:** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]Melted down. Used for scrap and spare parts. Purified.[[/span]]
>  
> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //**SCP-7478** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]chuckles[[/span]] again. It looms forwards, over **Elane**. Crouching to the ground and leaning on one knee, it places the empty box on the ground beside itself. **SCP-7478** reaches out and gently strokes **Elane's** hair.// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
>  
> **SCP-7478:** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]I know you are afraid. I am sorry that you believe that this is something you should fear.[[/span]]
>  
> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //**Elane** is still quietly sobbing into her arms. Her voice is choked with tears.// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
>  
> **Elane:** I- I don't- wh- why? Wh-why is this ha-appening to me?
>  
> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //**SCP-7478** gently reaches out and pulls her arms away from her face. It reaches towards her chin and angles it upwards so they are face-to-face. They hold eye contact, and **Elane's** expression betrays her panic, so rigid that her body is as heavy as stone.// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
>  
> **SCP-7478:** [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]Because you deserve it, Elane. You deserve to feel free.[[/span]]
>  
> [[=]]
> [[size 70%]] //The **something** lunges at **Elane**, landing on her chest before sinking through her clothing. She shrieks, clawing at it and attempting to gain purchase, but it slips through her fingers and her skin. **Elane** attempts to stand up and run, still pulling at her chest as she staggers into the darkness down a branching pathway of the tunnel. **SCP-7478** watches on as she flees. It is [[span style="filter: blur(4px);"]]smiling[[/span]].// [[/size]]
> [[/=]]
 
